# How to Run the Chat App (Full Steps)

## 1. Install Python 3.10+  
Download from python.org and make sure you check:
[âœ“] Add to PATH

---

## 2. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/cyberbot-ux/chat-app.git
cd chat-app

---

## 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

---

## 4. Start MongoDB using Docker
docker-compose up -d

(MongoDB will now run in the background)

---

## 5. Run the server
python server_code.py

(Server will show: "listening on 127.0.0.1:54678")

---

## 6. Run the client
python new_client.py

(The login/register window will open)

---

## 7. Create a test account
Use any name and a Gmail email.
Example:
Name: test_1
Email: test1@gmail.com
Password: something123

---

## 8. Create second test account
Name: test_2
Email: test2@gmail.com
Password: something123

Now you can DM between accounts.

---



## 9. Stop the server + MongoDB (optional)
docker-compose down
